Johannesburg – Orlando Pirates have confirmed the signing up of four player with the intent of bolstering their squad for the new PSL DStv Premiershp season. The Soweto giants announced the enlisting of the quad on their Twitter handle and the club’s website on Monday. “Orlando Pirates Football Club is pleased to announce the signing of Goodman Mosele, Monnapule Saleng, Bandile Shandu and Kwanda Mngonyama,” the club said. “Mosele joins the Club from Baroka FC on a four-year deal. The former PSL Young Player of the Season will join the Club upon his return from national duty at the Tokyo Olympics. “Attacking midfielder Saleng, who finished the season as Top Goal Scorer in the GladAfrica Championship, has signed an initial three-year deal. Meanwhile, Mngonyama and Shandu join as free agents on initial two-and three-year terms, respectively. Both players join having spent the 2020/21 season at Maritzburg United.” Also read: President’s daughter a vandal after ripping expensive clothes to shreds, claims ex Guptas stranded in Dubai as SA refuses to issue new passports Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World  